define({"topics" : [{"title":"All extension points","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The pre-defined extension points can be used to extend the functionality of the         DITA-OT. If your toolkit installation includes custom plug-ins that define additional extension points, you can         add to this list by rebuilding the DITA-OT documentation.</p>","href":"extension-points\/all-extension-points.html","attributes": {"data-id":"all-extension-points",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"all-extension-points-d50e1992","topics":[]},{"title":"General extension points","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">These extension points enable you to extend the DITA-OT. You can add Ant targets or imports; add a Java     library to the <span class=\"keyword parmname\">classpath</span> parameter; add a new transformation type; extend a catalog file; add     new diagnostic messages, and more.</p>","href":"extension-points\/plugin-extension-points-general.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-general-extension-points",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-general-extension-points-d50e2013","topics":[]},{"title":"Pre-processing extension points","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use these extension points to run an Ant target before or after the pre-processing stage. If     necessary, you can also run an Ant target before a specific pre-processing step â€” but this approach is not     recommended.</p>","href":"extension-points\/plugin-extension-points-pre-processing.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-extension-points-pre-processing",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-extension-points-pre-processing-d50e2037","topics":[]},{"title":"XSLT-import extension points","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use these extension points to override XSLT processing steps in pre-processing and certain     transformation types. The value of the <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlatt\">@file</code> attribute in the <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlelement\">&lt;feature&gt;</code>     element specifies a relative path to an XSL file in the current plug-in. The plug-in installer adds a XSL import     statement to the default DITA-OT code, so that the XSL override becomes part of the normal build.</p>","href":"extension-points\/plugin-extension-points-xslt-import.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-extension-points-xslt-import",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-extension-points-xslt-import-d50e2058","topics":[]},{"title":"XSLT-parameter extension points","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use theses extension points to pass parameters into existing XSLT steps in both the pre-processing     pipeline and DITA-OT transformation. The parameters generally will be available as global       <code class=\"keyword markupname xmlelement\">&lt;xsl:param&gt;</code> values with XSLT overrides.</p>","href":"extension-points\/plugin-extension-points-xslt-parameters.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-extension-points-xslt-parameters",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-extension-points-xslt-parameters-d50e2085","topics":[]},{"title":"Version and support information","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use these extension points to define version and support information for a plug-in. Currently, the     DITA-OT does not do anything with this information, but it might do so in the future.</p>","href":"extension-points\/plugin-extension-points-support.html","attributes": {"data-id":"plugin-support",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"plugin-support-d50e2109","topics":[]},{"title":"Plug-in extension points","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The default plug-ins that ship with the DITA Open Toolkit include a series of extension points that can be     used to modify various aspects of toolkit processing.</p>","href":"extension-points\/extension-points-by-plugin.html","attributes": {"data-id":"extension-points-by-plugin",},"menu": {"hasChildren":false,},"tocID":"extension-points-by-plugin-d50e2130","next":"extension-points-by-plugin-d50e2130",}]});